cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SY

The paper discusses the role of neurogenesis in artificial neural networks, which is a topic related to computational neuroscience and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also discusses the performance of dynamically grown networks in incremental learning scenarios, which is related to machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely categories as well. The paper also mentions the use of unsupervised learning, which is a common technique in computer vision, making cs.CV (Computer Vision) a possible category. Finally, the paper discusses the importance of preventing catastrophic forgetting in non-stationary environments, which is related to control systems and robotics, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) a possible category as well.
